stateDiagram-v2

    [*] --> Drafted

    Drafted     : title written and context drafted; not yet under review
    Proposed    : under team review; discussion captured; not yet binding
    Accepted    : decision binding; implementation underway or completed
    Deprecated  : not preferred for new work; existing usage may continue
    Superseded  : replaced by a specific newer ADR; document retained
    Rejected    : decision not adopted; document retained as evidence of the alternative considered

    Drafted     --> Proposed    : open for review
    Proposed    --> Accepted    : team consensus reached
    Proposed    --> Drafted     : feedback requires revision
    Proposed    --> Rejected    : decision not adopted
    Accepted    --> Deprecated  : approach no longer preferred
    Accepted    --> Superseded  : replaced by ADR-NNN
    Deprecated  --> Superseded  : replacement ADR now exists

    Superseded  --> [*]
    Rejected    --> [*]

    note right of Proposed
        Each status change appends to the
        document history with date and
        reason recorded. The ADR
        accumulates its own lifecycle log.
    end note

    note right of Superseded
        Bidirectional cross-link discipline:
        the superseded ADR points forward to
        its successor; the successor points
        back. The corpus stays navigable.
    end note
